Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, in a #saucepan{}, combine the @Finely Chopped Tomatoes with Basil{1%carton}, 
@Dried Basil{1%sachet}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g} and @Sugar{1%tsp}.

Bring to the boil.

Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into another saucepan with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Boil the @Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli{250%g}, ~{3%minutes}.

Drain and pop back in the pan.

Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through.

When the sauce is ready, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Stir in the @Butter{20%g}.

Remove from the heat.

Share the ravioli between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the tomato and basil sauce.

Drizzle over the @Fresh Pesto{32%g}, then sprinkle on the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%g}.

Serve the @Baby Leaf Mix{20%g} on the side with a drizzle of @olive oil{}.

Enjoy!